node.text:
If it’s your first time carrying a child or your 5th, you understand how the worry never goes away. ⁣⁣
I remember the long days between seeing a positive test to our first ultrasound. I thought once we heard a heartbeat we’d be “in the clear of worrying” and at relief. Then the worry came from 2 days in a row of not having morning sickness and wondering why, what was going?! So you worried again. Then one day the new worry was because I felt like my belly wasn’t growing overtime, and wondered why. Recently, having uncommon reactions with my body threw in a new worry of what was going on and if everything is OK. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Carrying this child is the most heart filling, exciting thing I’ve ever experienced but it’s also the most concerning, emotionally stressful thing. What I’ve realized of 17+ weeks of being a mother to a child is that the worry began and will never leave. There will always be a concern or worry being parent to something you love so dearly. But you worry because you care. You worry because you love your little baby so much already. As a mother, you have another life in your hands and that comes with so so much to face in a day. We wouldn’t trade it for the world, and it’s OK to feel your emotions through every season of being a momma. 🖤 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Grateful for another good doctors appointment and hearing a strong healthy heartbeat! You are loved so much already, baby P! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
P.s. Sharing our journey of finding out we were pregnant with our miracle because I haven’t shared yet 🙂 our full story is in my IGTV videos

node.text:
A question I get asked every morning is how I do my Bible study and how I deepened my faith in 2020. ⁣
I know if you got asked to remove one year of your life most would probably choose 2020.... but to be honest, 2020 was the most important year of my life thus far. It completely changed my faith, my view of life and every day circumstances, and my feelings as a person. When I started this Bible study and spent a half hour at the beginning of every day reading and understanding the Bible, my life changed more and more every single day. I searched for 25 years to find something that I would understand this well and guide me the way this app does. So I share this just in case there’s someone out there who needed this like I did, because if it wasn’t shared from a woman on social media I wouldn’t know about it 😞🙏🏼❤️⁣
The app: @thedailygraceco 
Bible:⁣ @valee_of_vision 
Bible tabs:⁣ Amazon
Devotion:⁣ Unshakable from Amazon
⁣
*I 100% respect everyone’s choice of faith and religion! This post is simply to just share what has worked for me and maybe for any other Christians wanting to deepen their faith or anyone wanting to understand the Bible better 💖 ⁣
P.s. video quality shows you how outdated my husbands phone is 🙈🤨

node.text:
It’s been awhile since I’ve showed how I make my smoothie! Honestly, I switch it up a lot! This has been my go to way to make it lately! I went live in my challenge group and shared this tutorial and now the ladies are hooked too ☺️ quite honestly, these ingredients don’t sound that great together but you👏🏽have👏🏽to👏🏽try👏🏽it! I’m a HUGE icecream lover so this hits the spot for me every single day. It’s that sweet milkshake I get but this one makes my body feel BETTER rather than worse. ⁣
⁣
*𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐦𝐨𝐭𝐞𝐬 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡𝐲 𝐰𝐞𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐥𝐨𝐬𝐬⁣
*𝐢𝐧𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐬 𝐞𝐧𝐞𝐫𝐠𝐲⁣
*𝐝𝐞𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐬 𝐜𝐫𝐚𝐯𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬⁣
*𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐞𝐬 𝐛𝐥𝐨𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠⁣
*𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡⁣
*𝐝𝐞𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐝 𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐨𝐥 & 𝐛𝐥𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐮𝐫𝐞 ⁣
*𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐞𝐬 𝐢𝐧𝐟𝐥𝐚𝐦𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 ⁣
*𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐢𝐦𝐦𝐮𝐧𝐞 𝐬𝐲𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐦⁣
*𝐢𝐧𝐜𝐥𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐬 𝐝𝐚𝐢𝐥𝐲 𝐯𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐬⁣
*𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡𝐲 𝐝𝐢𝐠𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧⁣
*𝐦𝐚𝐝𝐞 𝐟𝐫𝐨𝐦 𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐚𝐥 𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 ⁣
 ⁣
I’ve been consuming this daily for 38 months now and I’ll continue to stay committed 🥳👏🏽💪🏻💃🏼

Give it a try! 😊

Kate and I met through TikTok and now we have become good friends! We decided to have lunch together and chat it out! I also tried a new recipe that was SO GOOD! 

Flatout wrap in the airfryer for 7 mins at 375. Then top with avocado, chicken, feta cheese, and BBQ. Put back in airfryer for 5 mins! 🤤

node.text:
There’s no one in the world who loves chocolate dessert as much as I do. Chocolate icecream? YES PLEASE! 🙋🏼‍♀️⁣
⁣
I have this “𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦” EVERY single day at aprox 4pm when I’m dying for a treat and it’s helped me maintain my 65lb weight loss because I’ve been able to say no to the sugar loaded junk foods I used to have daily. It’s also my vitamin for the day which is a HUGE 𝐛𝐞𝐧𝐞𝐟𝐢𝐭 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐦𝐲 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐡. ⁣
⁣
*𝘊𝘶𝘱 𝘧𝘶𝘭𝘭 𝘰𝘧 𝘪𝘤𝘦⁣
*𝘈𝘱𝘳𝘰𝘹 𝟷.𝟻𝘤𝘶𝘱𝘴 𝘶𝘯𝘴𝘸𝘦𝘦𝘵𝘦𝘯𝘦𝘥 𝘷𝘢𝘯𝘪𝘭𝘭𝘢 𝘢𝘭𝘮𝘰𝘯𝘥 𝘮𝘪𝘭𝘬 (𝘰𝘳 𝘸𝘢𝘵𝘦𝘳)⁣
*𝟷 𝘴𝘮𝘢𝘭𝘭 𝘧𝘳𝘰𝘻𝘦𝘯 𝘣𝘢𝘯𝘢𝘯𝘢 ⁣
*𝟷 𝘴𝘤𝘰𝘰𝘱 𝘴𝘶𝘱𝘦𝘳𝘧𝘰𝘰𝘥𝘴 𝘱𝘰𝘸𝘥𝘦𝘳 (𝘰𝘳 𝘢𝘯𝘺 𝘱𝘳𝘰𝘵𝘦𝘪𝘯 𝘱𝘰𝘸𝘥𝘦𝘳) ⁣
*𝟸 𝘵𝘣𝘭𝘴 𝘗𝘉𝟸 𝘱𝘰𝘸𝘥𝘦𝘳 ⁣ @flavoredpbco *𝟷 𝘴𝘤𝘰𝘰𝘱 𝘥𝘪𝘨𝘦𝘴𝘵𝘪𝘷𝘦 𝘩𝘦𝘢𝘭𝘵𝘩 (𝘰𝘱𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯𝘢𝘭)⁣
⁣
𝘛𝘰𝘱 𝘸𝘪𝘵𝘩 𝘚𝘍 𝘤𝘩𝘰𝘤𝘰𝘭𝘢𝘵𝘦 𝘤𝘩𝘪𝘱𝘴 𝘰𝘳 𝘳𝘦𝘥𝘪𝘸𝘩𝘪𝘱 ⁣
⁣
Save this so you can make it and have your icecream every day while getting healthier at the same time 👏🏽👏🏽👏🏽 needing some this superfoods powder or digestive health? Message me! 💃🏼

node.text:
It’s crazy how fast time is already flying by with this little nugget, and I know it doesn’t slow down once they are in your arms🖤 I remember a few months ago my shower date feeling so far away, yet here we are and it was the most perfect day! A HUGE thank you to @brooke.mohnen @jessicakendres & @jesfrederick for everything they did making today absolutely amazing!! We are so blessed and thankful!! Showered in love and so excited to meet Baby Peters in September!
.
.
.

node.text:
The freedom of my being in control of my own work schedule with the flexibility like this is exactly what kept me in hustle mode building my business on the side of salon life 🙌🏻 The commitment and sacrifices are so worth it and I’m so glad I never gave up on my vision of what I wanted my days to look like. ☀️ ⁣
⁣
We had the best pool day and I love being their aunt more than they’ll ever know 🖤 ⁣
⁣
Can summer last forever? 🙏🏼
.
.
Swimsuit: @walmart & sunglasses are in the link in my bio if you swipe over to my amazon favs!

node.text:
Workouts are a lot like life in general.. some days you struggle hard, you feel weak, you feel like a beginner, you want to give up, you question why you showed up, you wonder if it’s worth it, you simply just don’t “feel it” that day….. but then you have days where you feel strong, you’re proud of yourself, you have high energy, you’re mood is up, you feel ambitious, you set goals even higher that day…⁣
⁣
Yesterday was a hard workout day for me and honestly my whole day was a little “down”, but today I feel strong as ever and was really feeling my workout. My daily reminder, no matter how I feel, is to show up…. Because honestly the days I don’t like it are the days I need it most. If I only showed up when I felt amazing and ambitious my consistency would be garbage, and consistency is the key to advancing forward towards change ✨ ⁣
⁣
Fun fact: I HATE leg day, it’s my least favorite day 😅 but it was on my workout calendar so I accepted the challenge and got it done. 28 minutes later feelin proud and strong! 🙌🏻🎉 I’ll share today’s workout in case you need a sweat sesh too! ⁣
⁣
𝐃𝐨 𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐦𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝟓𝟎 𝐬𝐞𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐝𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐚 𝟏𝟎 𝐬𝐞𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐝 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐢𝐧 𝐛𝐞𝐭𝐰𝐞𝐞𝐧. 𝐑𝐞𝐩𝐞𝐚𝐭 𝟐 𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐞𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐚 𝐭𝐨𝐭𝐚𝐥 𝐨𝐟 𝟑 𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝𝐬! ⁣
⁣
𝐆𝐨𝐛𝐥𝐞𝐭 𝐬𝐪𝐮𝐚𝐭⁣
𝐒𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐜 𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐠𝐞 (𝟑𝟎 𝐬𝐞𝐜 𝐞𝐚𝐜𝐡 𝐥𝐞𝐠) ⁣
𝐃𝐞𝐚𝐝𝐥𝐢𝐟𝐭⁣
𝗪𝐞𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐬𝐰𝐚𝐲 𝐬𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐠𝐞⁣
𝐀𝐥𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐠𝐞⁣
𝗪𝐞𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐠𝐥𝐮𝐭𝐞 𝐛𝐫𝐢𝐝𝐠𝐞 ⁣
⁣
Comment when you’ve done it 😃⁣
⁣

node.text:
⁣
𝐌𝐲 𝐬𝐭𝐨𝐦𝐚𝐜𝐡 𝐢𝐬 𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐫𝐫𝐫𝐫𝐲 𝐟𝐮𝐥𝐥, 𝐛𝐮𝐭 𝐦𝐲 𝐡𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐟𝐮𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐫 ☺️ ⁣
⁣
What a great past few days spending time with a few of my ladies and celebrating in Florida! 4 years ago I started this journey to get out of a personal rut I was in. I needed the spark and fire in my life that I saw others experiencing. I wasnt taking care of myself and I felt that urge to join the community. For so long I looked at those “girl tribes” and rolled my eyes saying I don’t need that, but wanna know something? It was deep down jealously for me. I saw them thriving. I saw them have eachother. I saw them being supported with positive energy daily. I saw them setting goals and visions and celebrating victories. And at the time I was struggling alone and not making progress so it was a deep down feeling of being left out. The moment I realized I NEEDED that and started taking care of my health with a community I saw change in who I was. I had the desire to show up daily. I found consistency. I enjoyed it vs dreaded it. I met new women daily and thrived off of new friendships. Here I am, 4 years later, mindblown at the women and the places the decision of yes has taken me 🙌🏻 Next year at this time I’ll be surrounded by thousands of women in this community for our annual event in St. Louis and I CANNOT WAIT! Say yes to opportunities, make the move. I promise if it’s on your heart and tugging you to do it, you’re suppose to 😉 I ignored that feeling for weeks, and then finally jumped in after too much watching with no action on my end. Cheers to my ladies who make this daily journey enjoyable and so much fun! 👯‍♀️

node.text:
I once saw this layout and it really was a light bulb for me and something I stand behind. It went like this: ⁣⁣
🥗🥗🍷🥗🥗⁣⁣
🥗🍟🥗🥗🥗⁣⁣
🥗🥗🍪🥗🥗⁣⁣
🥗🥗🥗🍩🥗⁣⁣
🥗🥗🥗🥗🍕⁣⁣
🥗🍫🥗🥗🥗⁣⁣
🥗🥗🍹🥗🥗⁣⁣
Vs this:⁣⁣
🥗🥗🥗🥗🥗⁣⁣
🥗🥗🥗🥗🥗⁣⁣
🥗🥗🥗🥗🥗⁣⁣
🥗🥗🥗🥗🥗⁣⁣
🥗🥗🥗🥗🥗⁣⁣
🍫🍕🍻🍩🍪⁣⁣
🍕🍷🍦🧁🍹⁣⁣
One question I get asked a lot is “do you ever have a cheat day?”. My response is “no”… because here’s the change I made a few years ago that made healthy living more enjoyable, sustainable, consistent, and permanent in my life rather than the miserable yo-yo dieting game” I’d play every few weeks. I thought it was “all in or nothing” kinda thing. No junk, no alcohol, tons of cardio and restricting otherwise I was failing and making no progress. The moment I started focusing on eating nutrient dense foods 90% of the time yet still having a small craving/treat often is when I found it a style of life. I move my body for 30 minutes a day following a workout calendar with a mix of weights/cardio/stretching depending on the day designed by a professional trainer. I found when I stopped the 100% all in mindset and went to the style of enjoying the Icecream, French fries, chips, or alcohol in small portions and in moderation frequently it was sustainable for me and I could stay consistent with eating healthy/nutrient foods to fuel my body and feel⁣⁣
good, yet enjoy those soul foods on the side. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So today, I enjoy this kid sized PB cup ice cream treat but also get to check off a completed workout, lots of water, my shakeology superfoods smoothie, and eating all colors of the rainbow throughout the day including veggies, fruits, protein, healthy fats, and fueling carbs ☺️ 𝐢𝐭’𝐬 𝐰𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐦𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐬 𝐦𝐞 𝐟𝐞𝐞𝐥 𝐠𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐤𝐬 𝐛𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐦𝐞!
